This project uses Tarn, a CLI API testing tool. Tests are .tarn.yaml files.

When writing API tests, use the .tarn.yaml format:

```yaml
name: Test name
steps:
  - name: Step name
    request:
      method: GET|POST|PUT|PATCH|DELETE
      url: "{{ env.base_url }}/path"
      headers:
        Content-Type: "application/json"
      body:
        key: "value"
    capture:
      var_name: "$.jsonpath"
    assert:
      status: 200
      body:
        "$.field": "expected"
        "$.field": { type: string, contains: "sub", not_empty: true }
```

Run tests: `tarn run`, `tarn run --format json`
Validate: `tarn validate`
List: `tarn list`

Assertion operators: eq, not_eq, type, contains, not_contains, starts_with, ends_with, matches, not_empty, exists, length, gt, gte, lt, lte.
Built-ins: {{ $uuid }} (alias for {{ $uuid_v4 }}), {{ $uuid_v4 }}, {{ $uuid_v7 }}, {{ $timestamp }}, {{ $now_iso }}, {{ $random_hex(n) }}, {{ $random_int(min, max) }}.
Faker built-ins (EN, seedable via TARN_FAKER_SEED or tarn.config.yaml faker.seed): {{ $email }}, {{ $first_name }}, {{ $last_name }}, {{ $name }}, {{ $username }}, {{ $phone }}, {{ $word }}, {{ $words(n) }}, {{ $sentence }}, {{ $slug }}, {{ $alpha(n) }}, {{ $alnum(n) }}, {{ $choice(a, b, ...) }}, {{ $bool }}, {{ $ipv4 }}, {{ $ipv6 }}.
Format assertions: is_uuid (any version), is_uuid_v4, is_uuid_v7, is_date, is_ipv4, is_ipv6.
Env resolution: --var > shell env > tarn.env.local.yaml > tarn.env.{name}.yaml > tarn.env.yaml > inline env:.
